{"application": "software-mentions", "version": "0.8.0", "date": "2024-10-07T11:58+0000", "md5": "4215E32CD8877026FDD439C08378A4DD", "mentions": [{"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Snoop", "normalizedForm": "Snoop", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 5}, "context": "Snoop then uses this information from the user to strengthen a model of the user's intention 34 . ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.033614397048950195}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.2993812561035156e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9986361861228943}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9942354559898376}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.42100316286087036}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Mediaset", "normalizedForm": "Mediaset", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 8}, "context": "Mediaset archives serve a dual purpose: to collect everything that has been shot by the broadcaster's personnel and to retain what was broadcast for potential future reuse.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.015906691551208496}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001780390739440918}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.9073486328125e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.947838544845581}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0942147970199585}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.00010371208190917969}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Distant Viewing Toolkit", "normalizedForm": "Distant Viewing Toolkit", "offsetStart": 18, "offsetEnd": 41}, "context": "For example, the \"Distant Viewing Toolkit\" (DVT), a Python toolkit for computational analysis of visual culture that addresses the challenge of working with moving images through automatic analysis such as narrative arcs detection 22 . ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 3.528594970703125e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.09397149085998535}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.152557373046875e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 3.528594970703125e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.09397149085998535}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.152557373046875e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Mediaset", "normalizedForm": "Mediaset", "offsetStart": 19, "offsetEnd": 27}, "context": "On the other hand, Mediaset stocks documents with different aims, not being interested, as a private player, to document broadcast programs for the aim of preservation.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00014197826385498047}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002263188362121582}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.947838544845581}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0942147970199585}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.00010371208190917969}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Snoop", "normalizedForm": "Snoop", "offsetStart": 22, "offsetEnd": 27}, "context": "By using the software Snoop, we not only intend to extend and validate our corpus, but more specifically to achieve the research of those hidden repetitions that we called ghost data, by: 1. Retrieving as many reuses of one specific video as possible, a step which plays a critical role in the process of drawing up the genealogies of the circulation in the media space of audiovisual archives; 2. For any shot, digging out the very first video including it, from which all the following videos derive, as it would enable us to compare new contexts (accompanying journalistic discourse, montage with other sequences in a news report, etc.) to the original one, so to understand the decontextualizationrecontextualization operated by journalists at each reuse.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.011666059494018555}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.13902300596237183}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.86102294921875e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9986361861228943}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9942354559898376}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.42100316286087036}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Snoop", "normalizedForm": "Snoop", "offsetStart": 23, "offsetEnd": 28}, "context": "Therefore, we consider Snoop as a relevant and reliable tool for retrieving good results, although a validation by humans will still be needed in a later step.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 9.572505950927734e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0012049674987792969}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.152557373046875e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9986361861228943}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9942354559898376}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.42100316286087036}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "PixPlot", "normalizedForm": "PixPlot", "offsetStart": 24, "offsetEnd": 31}, "version": {"rawForm": "23", "normalizedForm": "23", "offsetStart": 32, "offsetEnd": 34}, "context": "For example, we applied PixPlot 23 on our corpus. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999901056289673}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.3245811462402344e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999901056289673}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.3245811462402344e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Snoop", "normalizedForm": "Snoop", "offsetStart": 27, "offsetEnd": 32}, "context": "At the end of the process, Snoop provides us with a file in JSON format to download, in which the metadata of each positive result are contained. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.003090083599090576}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00037741661071777344}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1682510375976562e-05}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9986361861228943}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9942354559898376}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.42100316286087036}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Snoop", "normalizedForm": "Snoop", "offsetStart": 28, "offsetEnd": 33}, "context": "There is a possibility that Snoop finds us certain key frames from the same occurrence of a sequence.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00020128488540649414}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00039142370223999023}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9986361861228943}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9942354559898376}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.42100316286087036}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Snoop", "normalizedForm": "Snoop", "offsetStart": 33, "offsetEnd": 38}, "context": "Validation of frames by users on Snoop.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9877105355262756}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 4.3511390686035156e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9986361861228943}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9942354559898376}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.42100316286087036}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Snoop", "normalizedForm": "Snoop", "offsetStart": 36, "offsetEnd": 41}, "context": "Here, we admit that a limitation of Snoop is that it retrieves the key frame of a sequence at a two-second interval.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 8.71419906616211e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.017521560192108154}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9986361861228943}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9942354559898376}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.42100316286087036}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Snoop", "normalizedForm": "Snoop", "offsetStart": 38, "offsetEnd": 43}, "context": "During our first experimentation with Snoop, we managed to dig out a total of 119 occurrences of the stock shot about the signature of the Treaty of Rome. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9986361861228943}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.015137910842895508}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9986361861228943}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9942354559898376}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.42100316286087036}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Snoop", "normalizedForm": "Snoop", "offsetStart": 39, "offsetEnd": 44}, "context": "One of the key technological traits of Snoop is relevance looping, which allows for the creation of custom models for the visual entities, continuously amending the working models by including user input.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 3.0875205993652344e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.4762948751449585}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9986361861228943}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9942354559898376}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.42100316286087036}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Snoop", "normalizedForm": "Snoop", "offsetStart": 43, "offsetEnd": 48}, "context": "At last, we quickly presented the software Snoop, with the help of which we proceeded to increase the scope of our corpus, and we also aimed for reaching the original source of our stock footage.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.03272527456283569}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9942354559898376}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9986361861228943}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9942354559898376}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.42100316286087036}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Snoop", "normalizedForm": "Snoop", "offsetStart": 46, "offsetEnd": 51}, "context": "Based on a content-based detection technique, Snoop is an interactive visual search engine which is solicited by an initial input of a few images chosen by the user and representing their search intention. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00015044212341308594}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.005486965179443359}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.5497207641601562e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9986361861228943}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9942354559898376}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.42100316286087036}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Mediaset", "normalizedForm": "Mediaset", "offsetStart": 51, "offsetEnd": 59}, "context": "Thanks to our partnership with INA, Rai Teche, and Mediaset, we can obtain all the videos in our perimeter archived by these repositories. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004487097263336182}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.015069007873535156}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.00010371208190917969}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.947838544845581}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0942147970199585}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.00010371208190917969}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "implicit", "software-name": {"rawForm": "toolkit", "normalizedForm": "toolkit", "offsetStart": 59, "offsetEnd": 66}, "context": "For example, the \"Distant Viewing Toolkit\" (DVT), a Python toolkit for computational analysis of visual culture that addresses the challenge of working with moving images through automatic analysis such as narrative arcs detection 22 . ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 3.528594970703125e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.09397149085998535}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.152557373046875e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 3.528594970703125e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.09397149085998535}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.152557373046875e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Snoop", "normalizedForm": "Snoop", "offsetStart": 95, "offsetEnd": 100}, "context": "By feeding the software with the historical stock shots manually identified by us, we launched Snoop on a corpus of 6,000 news programs plus 56,000 new videos.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.5957371592521667}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.15472424030303955}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9986361861228943}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9942354559898376}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.42100316286087036}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Snoop", "normalizedForm": "Snoop", "offsetStart": 122, "offsetEnd": 127}, "context": "It therefore becomes necessary to employ an automatic detector of images, as the one in development at INA under the name Snoop.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 8.916854858398438e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.4562191367149353}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9986361861228943}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9942354559898376}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.42100316286087036}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Snoop", "normalizedForm": "Snoop", "offsetStart": 140, "offsetEnd": 145}, "context": "Anyway, in some cases, the original video source is available online or happens to be stocked in the database of our archival partners, and Snoop may effectively help us to find it.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00011420249938964844}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002446770668029785}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.42100316286087036}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9986361861228943}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9942354559898376}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.42100316286087036}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Mediaset", "normalizedForm": "Mediaset", "offsetStart": 204, "offsetEnd": 212}, "context": "A large part of our data comes from two national archives (the legal deposit of the French television kept at the INA, the audiovisual archives of the RAI in Italy) and a private deposit (the archives of Mediaset).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8859886527061462}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 6.711483001708984e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0728836059570312e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.947838544845581}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0942147970199585}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.00010371208190917969}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Snoop", "normalizedForm": "Snoop", "offsetStart": 221, "offsetEnd": 226}, "context": "The second way by which we want to validate the exhaustiveness of our corpus, is by automatically detecting more occurrences of the stock shots we already identified as pertinent in the full corpus, also with the help of Snoop.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.015441477298736572}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00026935338973999023}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9986361861228943}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9942354559898376}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.42100316286087036}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Mediaset", "normalizedForm": "Mediaset", "offsetStart": 259, "offsetEnd": 267}, "context": "In metaphorical terms, even if we could capture all the repetitions, we may lack access to the archived original incarnation of the \"ghost\" that is the video source, simply because it doesn't exist in the databases accessible to us (including INA, Rai Teche, Mediaset, Web archives, and the live web).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8292701244354248}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 7.605552673339844e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.474422454833984e-05}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.947838544845581}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0942147970199585}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.00010371208190917969}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Mediaset", "normalizedForm": "Mediaset", "offsetStart": 287, "offsetEnd": 295}, "context": "This paper is based on the research project Crossing Borders Archives (CROBORA), founded by the French National Research Agency, 2021-2024, led by the Sic.Lab at Universit\u00e9 C\u00f4te d'Azur in partnership with the French National Audiovisual Institute (INA), RAI (RadioTelevisione Italiana), Mediaset, Luxembourg University, the Catholic University of the Sacred Heart in Milan, the Universities of Lille, Paris Nanterre, and Paris Sorbonne.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.947838544845581}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0942147970199585}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.574920654296875e-05}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.947838544845581}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0942147970199585}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.00010371208190917969}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Mediaset", "normalizedForm": "Mediaset", "offsetStart": 321, "offsetEnd": 329}, "context": "First, our research field covers television in France and in Italy, which means the implication of multiple repositories of different natures: the French Legal Deposit of Web and Television, held by INA; the archives of the Italian public service of television, at RAI; and those of the main italian private broadcaster, Mediaset.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.015066206455230713}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.05295044183731079}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.1457672119140625e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.947838544845581}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0942147970199585}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.00010371208190917969}}}], "references": [], "runtime": 7979, "id": "c4a39dab7fb8537c5f11ed6ddea9ba932e5bbe0e", "metadata": {"id": "c4a39dab7fb8537c5f11ed6ddea9ba932e5bbe0e"}, "original_file_path": "../../datalake/Samuel/SOFTware-Sync/downloads/xml/hal-04233316.grobid.tei.xml", "file_name": "hal-04233316.grobid.tei.xml"}